  "description": [
    "Remember Work Day for the Orphanage Saturday September 17 Give your best work for one full day for the care of our 300 Orphan Children The recent disastrous fire destroying the dairy and involving a loss of some 12000 only half covered by insurance makes the call for general observance of Work Day more important MAKE IT A FAITHFUL DAY 686 and in 1925 83 The total num ber of children of school age in the United States is 29700000 The attendance upon high school has also greatly increased proportion ately It is shown that in 1890 only 16 per cent of graduates from gram mar school attended high school while in 1925 15 per cent of grammar school enrollment attended high school The average school term has also been considerably lengthened The average term in 1890 was 1347 school days In 1925 the average term was 1696 All this is encouraging Some may even feel like we have reached a real goal 2000000000 sounds like a lot of money Eighty three per cent of children of school age or approx imately twentyfive of the nearly thir ty million children of school age in the public schools sounds like we"
